Ambassador Linda Thomas-Greenfield led the U.S. delegation to the Pacific Islands Forum Leaders Meeting in Cook Islands on November 10. The Biden-Harris Administration is committed to enhancing the partnership with the Pacific Islands to achieve a resilient Pacific region of peace, harmony, security, social inclusion, and prosperity. The U.S. plans to provide over $8 billion in new funding and programs for the Pacific Islands. The United States recognizes the importance of tackling the climate crisis and helping Pacific Islands adapt to and manage the impacts of climate change. They are also committed to supporting economic development, building resilient infrastructure, promoting peace and security, and expanding people-to-people ties with the Pacific Islands.